I’d like to talk about a natural phenomenon that I found truly fascinating, which is the sunrise. Although it happens every day, I rarely get the chance to see it because I’m a bit of a night owl and don’t usually wake up early.

The first time I properly experienced a sunrise was about two years ago, when I went on a trip to Vũng Tàu with my family. One morning, they insisted that I wake up early and go to the beach with them to watch the sunrise. I was quite reluctant at first and almost decided to stay in bed, but I’m really glad I didn’t.

We arrived at the beach at around 5 a.m. and waited for the sun to rise. At first, the sky was still quite dark, with hints of purple and pink. Gradually, the colors became brighter, and as the sun slowly appeared on the horizon, its rays lit up the sky with beautiful shades of orange and gold. I even took out my phone to capture the moment because it was so breathtaking.

Standing there with my family, I felt a deep sense of peace and gratitude. It was such a simple yet powerful experience, and it made me realize how important it is to slow down and appreciate the beauty of nature.
